Package: circlss
Type: Package
Title: Circular-Response Location-Scale Families for 'mgcv'
Version: 0.0.3
Authors@R: person("Ziwei", "Huang", email = "huang-ziwei@outlook.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Circular-response distributional families for the 'mgcv'
    general family interface, so that gam() can fit penalized-spline
    regression models (GAM/GAMLSS) with an angular response. Provides the
    von Mises family vmlss(), with a Fisher-Lee tan-half link for the mean
    direction and a log link for the concentration, the projected
    normal family pnlss(), whose identity-linked Cartesian mean components
    let the fitted direction sweep and wind around the full circle, and
    the wrapped Cauchy family wclss(), the heavy-tailed counterpart of the
    von Mises with a logit-linked mean resultant length. Every
    distribution parameter is modelled by its own linear predictor;
    log-likelihood derivatives to fourth order support full Newton REML
    smoothing-parameter selection. Numerical results are differentially
    tested against the 'pycircstat2' Python package, whose derivative
    implementations this package transcribes.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    mgcv (>= 1.9.4),
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
